Why do you guys compare the actual numbers from the Coronavirus to the 2018-2019 numbers of people that got sick with influenza? I guess that would not attract viewers. Right?

CDC estimates that the burden of illness during the 2018–2019 season included an estimated 35.5 million people getting sick with influenza, 16.5 million people going to a health care provider for their illness, 490,600 hospitalizations, and 34,200 deaths from influenza (Table 1). snippet.textDisplay:
CALL TO WORSHIP                                  Psalm 95

Leader:  Come, let’s sing out loud to the Lord! Let’s raise a joyful shout to the rock of

              our salvation!

People: Let’s come before him with thanks! Let’s shout songs of joy to him!

Leader: The Lord is a great God, the great king over all other gods. The earth’s depths are

              in his hands; the mountain heights belong to him;

People: the sea, which he made, is his along with the dry ground, which his own

              hands formed.

Leader: Come, let’s worship and bow down! Let’s kneel before the Lord, our maker!

People: He is our God, and we are the people of his pasture, the sheep in his hands.

              If only you would listen to his voice right now!

Leader: “Don’t harden your hearts like you did at Meribah, like you did when you were

              at Massah, in the wilderness,

People: when your ancestors tested me and scrutinized me, even though they had

              already seen my acts.

Leader: For forty years I despised that generation; I said, ‘These people have twisted

              hearts. They don’t know my ways.’

People: So in anger I swore: ‘They will never enter my place of rest!’”

 

  UNISON PRAYER AND THE LORD’S PRAYER    

Lord, we have fallen far short of your purpose for us here, and we have sinned in so many ways. Forgive us for the times we have not heeded the guidance of your Holy Spirit. We have not centered our lives in your Son, Jesus Christ. Forgive us for the times when we have taken control of our own lives and stumbled. We have not been mindful of our behavior and how it could cause others to turn away from you. Forgive us for being mindful only of our own needs and neglecting the needs of others. Lord, in your loving mercy, grant us new life as we dedicate our lives once more to you. * We ask this through Jesus Christ, our Savior, who taught his disciples and us to pray: “Our Father…”
